					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/impperatrix" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7191955); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7191955&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610179171" alt="Impperatrix" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7191955)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/impperatrix" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7191955); return false;" >Impperatrix</a></span> <span class="odate time_1610178062 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Jan 2021 07:41</span>
																	<br/>
						in discussion <a href="/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-critique">Writing Help / Help: Ideas Critique</a> &raquo;
						<a href="/forum/t-13972674/sword-ballerina-seeking-greenlight">Sword Ballerina (Seeking Greenlight)</a>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4865750">
									

<p>I'm very happy with your reply as it helps a lot. There somethings that I've notice I <strong>HAVE</strong> to make clear and some that I have to correct based on your criticism. I'll take notes above as I'm going to sleep now, but I wanted to answer as fast as possible.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>The ballet dancing as a fighting style</strong> is something that only the automaton does, not the host. As you've said, it would be very difficult and hurtful to a human to do that. As the automaton is metallic and resistant, it would not hurt itself with it. I've imagined it fighting style not as ballet itself, but something as Pearl and Mega Pearl (Steven Universe), Fi (Zelda) and Bon Clay (One Piece), something based on the dance, but more aggressive, using flexibility and precision. I'm really confused as to how I can improve this and I accept some help. If it really has to be deleted, I'll be sad, I admit, but I want to make this work.</li>
<li><strong>The &quot;common agent&quot;</strong> thing is a communication error. It is a Foundation member anyway and took part in a mortal battle with a metallic sword lady. I'm having issues leveling it as I don't want the host to be a superhero but they are not an &quot;everyman&quot; stock character.</li>
<li><strong>The metallic human form</strong> is the SCP's &quot;defense mode&quot;. I didn't want the SCP to be a floating defending sword as there are already some floating weapon SCPs, so I've created this metal ballerina that is the host bastion while it is incapable of fighting by itself. If it really becomes an issue, I think it can be changed.</li>
<li><strong>About the host</strong>, the are almost guaranteed to be warriors as the directive for the SCP to change its host is killing the previous host or (if the host is already dead) defeating the SCP in battle. Both are very hard as both are based in fighting with the aforementioned &quot;Ultimate Warrior&quot;/&quot;Ultimate Weapon&quot;.</li>
<li><strong>About the mnestics/amnestics</strong>, the SCP is somehow a &quot;backup file&quot;. It's not as the SCP is resisting the amnestics, but it is recovering the host's memory. Is as if someone deleted everything in their computer, but there is an external HD with a backup that keeps being used to restore the computer data. The SCP is resilient to amnestics as it is a sword, it is inorganic, maybe an AI that the Foundation can't figure out how to reprogram. I don't really know if amnestics work on inorganic objects and if it works, I'll rethink this part.</li>
<li>Finally, <strong>about the SCP's backstory</strong> there is the mnestic experiment part. As the host is visiting previous owners' memories, it is discovering the SCP's rules, how it works and why it works this way. It seems simple, but there is this conundrum about exposing too much or too little of the SCP.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>

