<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>The concept:</strong><br />
Elevator Pitch: someone who was a regular person now considered something dangerous due to his ability to record audio with his mind and play the way he heard it out of his mouth sounding exactly the same.</p>
<p>While this does sound doable, I have trouble believing this would cause to him to be considered a danger. While the actions he <em>could</em> do have the potential to be dangerous, he himself isn't really a threat (at least not from what described).</p>
<p>Along with this, is there anything that really expands on what this is, or why it happened to him. Currently the skip feels like &quot;your average guy, but with a cool, unexplained power&quot;, as it doesn't seem like theres much behind the initial effects.- will the possible origins or purpose of the voice disc be elaborated on at all?</p>
<p><strong>The narrative:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Central Narrative: a person who was once a regular man woke up and looked in the mirror to discover a weird circular device stuck in his neck he tried to pull it off but couldnt.<br />
he tried to speak but then discovered he could sound exactly like singers of popular songs after singing scatmans world and even able to sing instrumental songs with his throat.<br />
for 3 months he kept this secret from friends and family.<br />
eventually the Foundation caught wind of this after investigating news papers from the subjects hometown about his ability and then later caught him after he was heard singing Michael Jacksons song thriller.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I second [[*user Grigori Karpin] in terms of the narrative, there isn't anything that shows what exactly happens after the skip gets contained. The narrative currently feels unfinished due to it being cut short right after the setup.</p>
<p>The narratives cut off also makes the skip itself feel a bit flat, as there isn't any time to really develop him or his ideals. There isn't much to get invested in here. What the narratives main conflict? what takes place after the skip is contained? whats everything building up to? how will the skip and its ideals affect the narrative?</p>
<p><strong>Red or green?</strong><br />
Due to my afore mentioned concerns, no-greenlight.</p>
<p>If you would like me review this (or any concept) further, then please feel free to send me a PM or ask via IRC. Response times generally range from 2-12 hours over PMs. If your looking for additional critiques/perspectives in general, then I would highly recommend contacting the butterfly squad :)</p>
</div>
