<p>Seeking Greenlights: Yes</p>
<p>Page Type: SCP Article</p>
<p>Elevator Pitch: What the summary says pretty much. We have an anomalous version of the <em>Fasciola hepatica</em> parasitic fluke. It worms its way into brains, and makes its hosts zombie-like in their pursuit of rubber. Plenty of rubber-related puns and jokes nestled in there (not super cheesy) for bonus containment points.</p>
<p>Central Narrative: Most of the narrative centers around the progression of the infection and symptom development. I also threw in an addendum about an outbreak at a NASCAR race which I think merges the humor of zombies at a raceway with the detached view of The Foundation in a humorous way.</p>
<p>Hook/Attention-Grabber: There are honestly relatively few biological SCPs that aren't extremely different from real world creatures. I understand why, because doing something that feels realistic is definitely more difficult and takes some of the fun out of the fantasy aspect. However, I think I could fill the lack of high-realism bio-SCPs if I work at it hard enough. I get big into the details of scientific stuff like this, so I think I can pull it off really well.</p>
<p>Additional Notes: I have already written up the entire page. I felt I could only elaborate on the realism aspect I am going for by doing the research and writing the whole thing to make sure it fit nicely. I know there are rules about posting the sandbox links unprompted, so if you are interested in seeing what I've done just ask.</p>

